<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
The synonymy of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. schneideri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="schneideri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. schneideri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. liogaster" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="liogaster">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. liogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lindqvist, E" journalOrPublisher="Notulae Entomologicae" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="72 - 76" refId="B109" refString="Lindqvist, E, 1943. Zur Kenntnis einiger Tenthrediniden. Notulae Entomologicae 23: 72 - 76" title="Zur Kenntnis einiger Tenthrediniden." volume="23" year="1943">Lindqvist (1943)</bibRefCitation>
. Treated here as a color form of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. liogaster" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="liogaster">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. liogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but still separated in the key, because the melanic color form of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. liogaster" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="liogaster">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. liogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has black legs, and 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. schmidti" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="schmidti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. schmidti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a color form with a red-marked thorax. Specimens resembling 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. schneideri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="schneideri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. schneideri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are also known from the mountain areas of Central Europe, e.g. from Switzerland at altitudes of 1500-1700 m (
<bibRefCitation author="Benson, RB" journalOrPublisher="Ergebnisse der wissenschaftlichen Untersuchungen im Schweizerischen Nationalpark" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="161 - 195" refId="B13" refString="Benson, RB, 1961. The sawflies (Hymenoptera Symphyta) of the Swiss National Park and surrounding Area. Ergebnisse der wissenschaftlichen Untersuchungen im Schweizerischen Nationalpark 7: 161 - 195" title="The sawflies (Hymenoptera Symphyta) of the Swiss National Park and surrounding Area." volume="7" year="1961">Benson 1961</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Lacourt" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus truncatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus truncatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lacourt, 1988. The holotype (CTN) was studied. Its clypeus emargination looks as if it is abnormally developed. The penis valve (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Dolerus truncatus Lacourt, 1988, holotype (? = D. liogaster). Penis valve." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719529" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">18</figureCitation>
) appears to be somewhat distorted, perhaps during preparation, but resembles the valve of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. liogaster" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="liogaster">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. liogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Tentatively, we treat 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. truncatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="truncatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. truncatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. liogaster" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="liogaster">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. liogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
